entry.title: Fix wrong backface visibility of composited layer under 3d transforms
entry.content:
In blink:

- Change the condition in PaintPropertyTreeBuilder for inheriting

parent backface visibility. Now a transform node inherits parent

backface visibility if there is the parent doesn't preserve 3d and

the current LayoutObject doesn't have 3d transform properties.

has no effect because TransformNode::delegates_to_parent_for_backface

entry.title: win: Experiment setting MEMORY_PRIORITY_NORMAL in background threads
entry.content:
We are observing an issue where memory allocated by background threads

is being created at pri-1 (very close to paging out), and

referred to by higher-priority threads. This is an issue, because

that memory then gets paged out, causing faults in high-priority code

and creating contention.



For context, when memory enters the resident set of a user-blocking

thread, it enters at pri-5. This is what is wanted, and signifies memory

being 'in use' in a standard way.

entry.title: [Hub] Create FadeHubLayoutAnimationFactory
entry.content:
Implement the fade animations for HubLayout. Also add an afterEnd stage

to the listener so that the animation state can be reset after the

animation finishes. This happens after HubLayout has set the state of

the view to its final state. The benefit of this new event is:



1) It makes the state changes happen in the expected order even though

all the events are synchronous so no onDraw will happen between onEnd

and afterEnd. So even though this doesn't matter from a UI change

perspective, the internal states are consistent.

2) It makes it possible to test both the state of the animation

after the animation ends and the state in afterEnd to confirm both

the final animation state and state after resetting and values used

during animation are both correct.

setDecorFitsSystemWindows so we do not propagate onApplyWindowInsets

notifications to classes like InsetObserverView.java. Those

notifications could have performance implications since they are sent

through a depth-first traversal of the view hierarchy.

and subsequently just adjust the padding and associated rendering to

switch back and forth between ToNormal and ToEdge.

needed notifications during a page reload.

entry.title: Add flag to bypass HSTS and use for AIA, CRL, and OCSP requests.
entry.content:
We were previously hitting an issue where AIA, CRL, and OCSP requests

were being upgraded to HTTPS, as the URLs were hosted by domains

that had HSTS applied. These requests should not ever be upgraded,

in order to avoid circular dependencies when verifying certificates.



We solve this by adding a new load_flag "should_bypass_hsts" which we

set to true whenever making AIA, CRL, or OCSP requests. We then check

for this flag when deciding whether or not to upgrade an HTTP request.





Added tests to ensure HSTS was bypassed even if a domain is set to

have HSTS and also tested round-tripping of setting load_flags in

a URL Request.

entry.title: Make document.fonts.check() in conformance with the updated spec.
entry.content:
The document.fonts.check() neither behaves as the current spec document

describes [1] nor other rendering engines behave. First, the

FontFaceSet::check() should return true for non-existent fonts [2].

Second, the check method should not reveal any platform fallback font

existence. Third, the existing implementation does not follow the

updated checking steps (e.g., checking the range intersection with the

given text is inefficient and erroneous, where all found font faces

support the same character set). So, this CL re-implements

document.fonts.check(), conforming to the standard and other engines'

behaviors.



[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/css-font-loading/#font-face-set-check

[2] https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/5744

entry.title: Update ProxyDelegate to handle proxy chains
entry.content:
ProxyDelegate handles both proxy failure, and headers sent to specific

proxies. Instead of getting a ProxyServer, it now gets a ProxyChain with

an index indicating the specific server involved. This allows

implementers to recognize either the full chain (e.g., for fallback from

chain to chain) or a specific server (e.g., to send authorization

headers to that server).



The NetworkServiceProxyDelegate::Observer, which has many of the same

methods, remains in terms of ProxyServer; this will be addressed in a

further CL.

entry.title: Begin adding ProxyChains

A ProxyChain represents a series of proxies to connect one-to-the-next.



This CL begins by adding a new ProxyChain class which is always a chain

of length 1, and updating ProxyList to contain a list of ProxyChains. To

maintain compatibility, all existing ProxyServer-related ProxyList

methods remain.



The trickiest of these was `GetAll`, since it is `const` and returns a

reference to a vector. Supporting this requires maintaining a parallel

vector of ProxyServers. Once the `GetAll` is removed, this field can be

removed as well.

entry.title: [omnibox][ml] Skip annotating match rather than return early when not
entry.content:
found in history DB.



Previously, when a match's destination_url was not found in the db,

the history annotator would return early. However, this was called in

a loop that iterated over multiple matches. This meant that the rest of

matches in the resul would not get the chance to be annotated, even if

the signals were available. This might have led to lower coverage for

the history scoring signals than is actually possible with the in-memory

database.



This CL fixes this issue and updates the unit test to check for this

situation.

entry.title: Remove PrefetchService::prefetch_ready_to_serve_
entry.content:
This CL removes `PrefetchService::prefetch_ready_to_serve_`

and thus the requirements for serving via

`PrefetchDocumentManager::DidStartNavigation()` ->

`PrefetchService::PrepareToServe()` -> `prefetch_ready_to_serve_`.



The major checks contributing to the `prefetch_ready_to_serve_`

has already removed during the effort of https://crbug.com/1448731,

and thus the matching behavior isn't conceptually affected,

while there can be minor differences.



This enables serving PrefetchContainer in the cases that

haven't been going through corresponding `DidStartNavigation()`

calls, e.g. https://crbug.com/1432886.

Such cases are still Document-scoped, because of

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4919824.

They are not benefited by the early cookie copy starting

in `PrefetchDocumentManager::DidStartNavigation()`, but

anyway it's better than not serving.



Bug: 1432886, 1448731, 1430334

entry.title: [//gpu] Add ConvertYUVAMailboxesToTexture() API
entry.content:
We will use this API to implement one-copy VideoFrame->WebGL texture

upload for legacy multiplanar SharedImage and pure software

VideoFrames (currently these cases go through legacy mailboxes to

implement 1-copy VideoFrame->WebGL texture upload).



The underlying implementation in copy_shared_image_helper.cc will

follow that of ConvertYUVAMailboxesToRGB(), but adapted as necessary to

match CopySharedImageToGLTexture(). As of this CL it is stubbed out. We

will implement this method only for the passthrough decoder, as the

implementation relies on doing service-side GL operations via Skia, and

manually saving/restoring WebGL's service-side GL state is not worth it

considering that the validating decoder will shortly be used only on

Android, which has the 1-copy path disabled.
